In a bowl, cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; stir in pecans. Press into an ungreased 13-in. x 9-in x 2-in. baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 15 minutes. Combine rhubarb, sugar and flour; spoon over the crust. Bake for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Pour over hot rhubarb layer. Bake for 30 minutes. Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla; spread over hot cheesecake. Cool on wire rack for 1 hour. Refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle with additional pecans if desired.